---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/url';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="ReefMetric privacy policy.">
  <section class="container" style="max-width:760px;">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--brand-2)">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: July 2026.</em></p>
    <p>ReefMetric respects your privacy. This page explains what we collect and why.</p>
    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>We use Cloudflare Web Analytics to see how many people visit and which pages they read. It's cookieless and privacy-first: no cookies, no persistent identifiers, no cross-site tracking, no personal data collected — Cloudflare measures traffic using aggregated, anonymized signals instead. If you subscribe to our email list, we also collect the address you provide and never sell it.</p>
    <h2>Cookies &amp; consent</h2>
    <p>ReefMetric sets no cookies of its own, and our analytics doesn't use them either — so there's nothing to consent to and no banner is required under GDPR or similar laws, which specifically target cookies and persistent tracking identifiers. When you click a "Check price" link, you leave ReefMetric for the retailer's site, and that retailer may set its own cookies under its own privacy policy — that's between you and them, not us. If that ever changes — if we add cookie-based tracking of any kind — this page updates first, and EU/UK visitors would see a consent banner before any tracking cookie is set.</p>
    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>Some links are affiliate links — see our <a href={url('/disclosure')}>Affiliate Disclosure</a>.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Reach us at <a href="mailto:hello@reefmetric.com">hello@reefmetric.com</a>.</p>
  </section>
</Base>
